singhski 2025-03-21 03:16 p.m.
PAPERLESS ORDER ENTERING PLEA DEAL

In the criminal matter of;
State of Mayflower v. UN61433408

Date of Judgement: 03/20/2025

The following parties appeared:
Prosecution: LachieScripts, Funpark22
Defense: UN61433408, JamesMHamilton

The State has charged the Defendant with:
Count One - 1 M.S.C. 2101 First-degree Murder Count Two - 1 M.S.C. 2301 Attempted murder Count Three - 1 M.S.C. 2302 Assault with a Deadly Weapon on two counts Count Four - 1 M.S.C. 3104 Grand theft Count Five - 1 M.S.C. 3207 Trespass on military property Count Six - 1 M.S.C. 6102 Unlicensed possession of a firearm Count Seven - 1 M.S.C. 6013 Unlicensed possession of a high-capacity magazine


The Court finds the Defendant guilty of:
1 M.S.C. 2101 First-degree Murder 1 M.S.C. 2301 Attempted murder 1 M.S.C. 2302 Assault with a Deadly Weapon on two counts 1 M.S.C. 6102 Unlicensed possession of a firearm 1 M.S.C. 6013 Unlicensed possession of a high-capacity magazine


PLEA AGREEMENT
Both the prosecution and defense have agreed to a plea agreement, which the Court approves. Within this agreement, the Defendant shall plead guilty to one count of first-degree murder, one count of attempted murder, two counts of assault with a deadly weapon, one count of unlicensed possession of a firearm, and one count of unlicensed possession of a high-capacity magazine. In accordance with the plea agreement, the charges of grand theft and trespass on military property are dismissed.

The State agrees that no additional charges arising from the same incident shall be filed against the Defendant. The Defendant acknowledges that any violation of laws during or after incarceration may result in enhanced penalties for future offenses.


/s/ Singhski
District Court Judge
